<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="multi-waffles" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Multigrain Waffles</title>

  <p>
    Ingredients:
  </p>
  <tabular>
    <row>
      <cell>2 cups whole-wheat flour</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>1 cup cornmeal</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell><m>\frac{1}{2}</m>cup oats</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
    <cell>1 tablespoon honey</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>1 tablespoon baking powder</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell><m>\frac{3}{4}</m> teaspoon baking soda</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell><m>\frac{1}{2}</m> teaspoon salt</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>5 eggs (or 3 eggs and 4 egg whites)</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>3 cups milk (or buttermilk)</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell><m>\frac{1}{2}</m> cup applesauce</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>3 tablespoons canola oil</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>5 tablespoons butter, melted</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>1 teaspoon vanilla extract (optional)</cell>
    </row>
  </tabular>

  <p>Instructions
    <ol>
      <li>
        <p>
          Mix dry ingredients together.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Mix wet ingredients together.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Pour wet ingredients into dry ingredients. Mix until just combined.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Cook on the waffle iron.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </p>

  <p>
    Notes:
    <ul>
      <li>
        <p>
          Original recipe called for 3 eggs and 4 egg whites.  I changed that to 5 eggs so I didn't have to deal with 4 orphan egg yolks.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          This makes a lot of waffles.  You can make smaller batches according to how many eggs you put in (e.g. a <m>\frac{2}{5}</m> recipe with 2 eggs).
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </p>
</section>